EXTRACTED VALUE: There are a lot of good ideas contained in Frontlines: Fuel of War, but their execution just seems to make the game feel average.
The game is worth buying and will offer gamers hours of fun, whether it is creating custom wrestlers or fighting for your life in the career mode.
The game offers an intriguing story which spices things up very well, but it does so without doing anything revolutionary.
The infrastructure is definitely in place for a corker of a kickabout but the important thing - that intangible soul - is still frustratingly missing.
Visually, NHL 07 is a bit crisper and cleaner in high-definition.
There're no stunning next-gen visuals to be found, and it doesn't help that it has such strong competition to live up to from its own predecessors.
Do you like football games? If the answer is yes, then purchase it, if the answer is no, then dont.
A brilliant game that no 360 gamer should ignore.
